definitions.definition: To wrap something up into the form of a package .
To wrap a strip around the end of a rope .
examples: Worm and parcel with the lay ; turn and serve the other way.

definitions.definition: To divide and distribute by parts or portions; often with off , out or into .
To add a parcel or item to; to itemize .
